        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-08-20 05:00:57.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi Renu, what are your plans as the layer architecture failure is not really related to this story ?\nShould we first do a package move refactoring, if we all agree for it? And then, once it is done, we implement the async feature in a different change ? Having the aync change alone can definitively help for its understanding I think.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "fbac4971c818abeb8439a0eb87d6a4d14eebb42c",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 5658,
          "name": "Bruno Sakoto",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "bruno.sakoto@bell.ca",
          "username": "brusak"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2021-08-20 05:16:29.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nYou can also try something else: try to delete your local cps-application/archunit_store folder and re-run the tests, layer architecture should not fail anymore on your local environment. And because this folder is not under source control it is possible that it won't fail on jenkins neither if it starts a clean workspace for each build.\n\nIf ever this works, you will be able to move ahead with your change and layer architecture issues could be fixed after.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
